Package br.eti.villani

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Building
    Creates four ARFF bases for each subset.
    BuildingAxes
    From each theses fourth bases will be getted more four sub-bases.
    Evaluating
    In each iteration, the ARFF bases are used of the following way:
    Each base from each extractor features must be the train set used to create the classifier's model.
    EvaluatingAxes
    In this evaluation, only labels from a unique axis is maintained beyond the features.
    Main
    This framework provide a way to use the features extract techniques and multi-labels learners to automatic classification of two-dimensional medical images.
    Preparing
    Gets the images subsets, without reposition and without TIF extension, from IRMA images set.
    Tabulating
    Group by measure the results from iterations of the direct classification axes of the IRMA code.
    TabulatingAxes
    Group by measure the results from iterations of the axis-to-axis classification of the IRMA code.
